casebody.data:
Neal A. NORLES, Appellant,
v.
STATE of Missouri, Respondent. WD 80211 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: JANUARY 30, 2018 Attorneys: Christian Lehmberg, Columbia, MO, Counsel for Appellant. Attorneys: Gregory L. Barnes, Jefferson City, MO, Counsel for Respondent. Before Division Two: Anthony Rex Gabbert, Presiding Judge, Thomas H. Newton, Judge, Gary D. Witt, Judge

ORDER

Per Curiam:

Neal A. Norles appeals from a judgment denying his Rule 24.035 motion for post-conviction relief without an evidentiary hearing after he pleaded guilty to the class B felony of possession of a controlled substance with the intent to distribute in violation of Section 195.211, RSMo Cum. Supp. 2003. We affirm. Rule 84.16(b).
